input:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant BaldEagle : obj
constant Dog : obj
constant Rabbit : obj
constant Squirrel : obj

constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Likes : obj → obj → Prop
constant Sees : obj → obj → Prop
constant Cold : obj → Prop
constant Visits : obj → obj → Prop
constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Blue : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Round BaldEagle
axiom T2 : Likes BaldEagle Dog
axiom T3 : Likes BaldEagle Rabbit
axiom T4 : Sees BaldEagle Squirrel
axiom T5 : Cold Dog
axiom T6 : Likes Dog BaldEagle
axiom T7 : Likes Dog Rabbit
axiom T8 : Visits Dog BaldEagle
axiom T9 : Green Rabbit
axiom T10 : Visits Rabbit Squirrel
axiom T11 : Cold Squirrel
axiom T12 : Rough Squirrel

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x BaldEagle ∧ Likes BaldEagle Rabbit → Likes Rabbit Dog
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Sees Squirrel BaldEagle ∧ Visits Squirrel Rabbit → Visits Rabbit BaldEagle
axiom R3 : Blue Dog → Sees Dog BaldEagle
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Likes x Dog → Cold x
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Cold x → Blue x

theorem rabbit_is_blue : Blue Rabbit :=
begin
  sorry,
end
output:
theorem rabbit_is_blue : Blue Rabbit :=
begin
  apply R5,
  apply R4,
  apply R1,
  split,
  exact T4,
  exact T3,
end
